Mohale Motaung’s revelation about his therapy session has not garnered support or love from many social media users. Motaung, who went through a nasty break-up with his estranged husband Somizi Mhlongo, shared on social media that he started therapy a year ago. He also revealed that he has been to therapy for 52 days to date. “I’m happy, hurting, and healing at the same time. Don’t ask me how I’m doing it because I don’t know, but I’m doing it, and I’m so proud of myself,” he wrote. Mental health has become something many celebrities are taking seriously with Mohale being the latest to share his therapy journey.        Also Read: I’ve always been a tea lover, says Mohale on joining popular brand For the latest entertainment news from Sunday World, click here. Or read the latest from Shwashwi here. Follow @SundayWorldZA on Twitter and @sundayworldza on Instagram, or like our Facebook Page, Sunday World, by clicking here for the latest breaking news in South Africa. To Subscribe to Sunday World, click here.